---
import ServicePage from "../components/ServicePage.astro";
import { SERVICES } from "../lib/site.js";
const service = SERVICES.find((s) => s.url === "/towing-and-vehicle-recovery-anna-tx/");
const faqs = [
  { q: "What types of vehicles can you tow in Anna?", a: "Cars, pickups, SUVs, vans, and motorcycles are all handled on a flatbed or wheel-lift. Lowered, all-wheel-drive, and non-running vehicles ride on a flatbed so the wheels never touch the road." },
  { q: "Can you tow my car to a shop outside Anna?", a: "Yes. Many drivers ask for a tow to a shop or dealer in McKinney or elsewhere along US-75. You pick the destination and get the distance priced upfront before the truck rolls." },
  { q: "My car is stuck off the road. Can you recover it?", a: "Yes. Winch-outs from a ditch, a soft shoulder, or a yard are part of the job. Tell the dispatcher how the vehicle is sitting so the right truck and gear come out." },
  { q: "How soon can a tow truck arrive?", a: "Anna is small enough that a local operator is usually minutes away. You get an honest time estimate when you call, based on your location and current road conditions." },
];
---
<ServicePage
  service={service}
  title="Towing & Vehicle Recovery in Anna, TX"
  description="Local 24/7 towing and vehicle recovery in Anna, TX. Flatbed and wheel-lift tows for cars, trucks, SUVs, and motorcycles, plus winch-outs. Call (214) 491-5215."
  hero="/images/hero-recovery.webp"
  heroAlt="Flatbed tow truck loading a sedan on an Anna, TX street"
  lede="Hooked up, loaded with care, and taken where you need it. A local Anna operator handles cars, trucks, SUVs, and motorcycles around the clock."
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <p class="lead-p">When your vehicle quits on you in Anna, a tow should be the easy part of a bad day.</p>
  <p>Call Anna Towing and you reach a local tow operator who works this town every day. Whether you are stalled at a light on US-75, sitting in a parking lot at Anna Town Square, or stuck in a driveway out in West Crossing, a truck is dispatched from nearby and arrives with the right equipment for your vehicle.</p>

  <h2>Flatbed and wheel-lift towing</h2>
  <p>Most vehicles in Anna ride best on a flatbed. The whole car sits on the bed, so the wheels never touch the road and there is no extra strain on the transmission or suspension. That matters for lowered cars, all-wheel-drive vehicles, classics, and anything that will not roll. For standard front-wheel-drive cars and short hops across town, a wheel-lift can be the quick, clean option. The operator brings the setup that fits your vehicle and your situation.</p>

  <h2>Vehicle recovery and winch-outs</h2>
  <p>Anna gets its share of rain, and the ground off the shoulder turns soft fast. If your vehicle has slid into a ditch off FM-455, dropped a wheel on a gravel edge near Ferguson Parkway, or buried itself in a muddy lot, a winch-out gets it back on solid ground without tearing up the underside. Describe how the vehicle is sitting when you call so the operator arrives ready.</p>

  <h2>Local and longer-distance tows</h2>
  <p>Plenty of Anna tows are short, a few minutes to a trusted mechanic in town or over to a shop in McKinney. Others run farther, up to a dealer or a body shop along the US-75 corridor. Either way you choose the destination, and the distance is quoted upfront so the price is clear before anyone hooks up your car.</p>

  <h2>Why Anna drivers call local</h2>
  <p>A tow operator who already knows Anna does not need to be talked through the streets. They know that West White Street and East White Street are both FM-455, that Rosamond Parkway runs past the high school, and that the Villages of Hurricane Creek sit on the west side of town. That familiarity turns into a shorter wait and a smoother pickup. Every tow is handled by a licensed and insured operator, and you get a straight estimate before the work starts.</p>
</ServicePage>
